ἓ “ Scipio Africanus. '² This passage has given infinite trouble to the commentators. Ennius (denoted here by the “ Calabrian Muses'') cele- brated the elder Scipio. But Carthage was burned, not by the elder Scipio, but by the younger Scipio Africanus, many years after the death of Ennius 3 and it cannot be supposed that Horace was so ignorant as to ascribe to the elder Scipio the act of the younger. It was even proposed by Bentley to omit the seventeenth verse, referring to Carthage, alto- gether ; but the line is in all the MSS. extant.
